com.bigdata.rdf.store

Class BigdataTriplePatternMaterializer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bigdata.striterator.AbstractChunkedResolverator<BigdataTriplePattern,ISPO,AbstractTripleStore>
      • com.bigdata.rdf.store.BigdataTriplePatternMaterializer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICloseable, ICloseableIterator<ISPO>, Iterator<ISPO>

    public class BigdataTriplePatternMaterializer
extends AbstractChunkedResolverator<BigdataTriplePattern,ISPO,AbstractTripleStore>
implements ICloseableIterator<ISPO>
    Efficient batched, streaming resolution of triple patterns to statements spanned by those triple patterns that are present in the data.

    Note: If the input contains triple patterns that have a high cardinality in the data, then a large number of statements may be returned.

    See Also:
    Efficient batch remove of a collection of triple patterns

      • start

        public BigdataTriplePatternMaterializer start(ExecutorService service)
        Description copied from class: AbstractChunkedResolverator
        Creates and runs a task that will consume chunks from the source iterator, resolve the elements in each chunk, and place the resolved chunks onto the BlockingBuffer.

        You MUST invoke this before consuming results from the iterator.

        Implementations SHOULD strengthen the return type.

        Overrides:
        start in class AbstractChunkedResolverator<BigdataTriplePattern,ISPO,AbstractTripleStore>
        Parameters:
        service - The service on which the task will be executed.
